{
  "texts": [
    "However, as many inference serving systems require latencybounded execution, we have to forgo the sub-network selection technique based on the input content, especially in the batching scenario where inputs in the batch can have different content.",
    "That means we miss an opportunity to optimize the sub-network selection for accuracy.",
    "Another method to enable dynamic DNN execution is to exit early from the DNN (a.k.a.",
    "early-exit DNNs, as illustrated in Fig. 5b), when the input data is easy to infer, thereby amortizing the computational cost (Teerapittayanon et al. 2016).",
    "To that end, we need to place exit branches at intervals along the base DNN to decide and exit when partial execution up to the exit point is confidently accurate in its prediction."
  ]
}